The paper deals with algorithmic bounds for terminal-clustering problems, which are a type of optimization problem in metric spaces. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), cs.GT (computational game theory), and cs.SI (social and information networks). The focus on metric spaces and clustering also suggests that the paper may not be directly related to topics such as computer vision or machine learning, which are more commonly associated with other arXiv CS sub-categories.
